## Scenario

You are building an automated essay feedback system for a secondary school. Teachers
submit student essays and receive a structured assessment report: scores across three
dimensions (content, structure, language), specific strengths and weaknesses, and
actionable suggestions for improvement.

The system must be consistent — the same essay should receive the same score
regardless of when it is submitted — and never fabricate examples that do not appear
in the essay.

