## Success criteria

### Domain 1 — Agentic Architecture & Orchestration
- [ ] The agentic loop in `grade_essay` checks `stop_reason` and only terminates on `"end_turn"`
- [ ] `run_subagent` passes essay text directly in the prompt — it does not rely on shared context
- [ ] `post_tool_use_hook` intercepts tool results *before* aggregation, not after
- [ ] The hook clamps scores programmatically — it does not add a prompt instruction to fix the score
- [ ] Each subagent only receives the tool relevant to its role (content tool to content agent, etc.)

### Domain 4 — Prompt Engineering & Structured Output
- [ ] `tool_choice` forces the specific tool by name on every API call
- [ ] `improvement_example` is NOT in the `required` array
- [ ] Each subagent system prompt includes 2 few-shot scoring examples
- [ ] Each subagent description says "Flag ONLY" and "Do NOT flag" with specific exclusions
- [ ] The validation-retry error message names the specific mismatch (actual vs expected score) — not "invalid result"
- [ ] E003 (Priya) scores at least 2 points higher than E002 (Ben) on content

